FACTS: Founder and director of the Observatory of Comes.
GENERAL: Damaged circular formation.
SLOPES: Few steep slopes supporting Cichus to the South-West Cichus J & B to the South.
WALLS: Few high walls gobbled to the North.
FLOOR: Flat floor filled with lava supporting Weiss E to the North. Grooves and hills. Craterlets.

NAME: WERNER
PERIOD: Eratosthenian (From -3.2 billions years to -1.1 billions years)
GENERAL: Young circular formation forming an interesting couple with Aliacensis.
SLOPES: Very steep and tormented slopes supporting Blanchinus to the North Aliacensis to the South-East and Regiomontanus to the West.
WALLS: Walls in very raised tiers supporting the craterlet Werner D to the North.
FLOOR: Flat floor but tormented alongside the South wall. Slightly off-centered mountain.

NAME: WEXLER
PERIOD: Birth period not found
FACTS: meteorological satellite Specialist.
GENERAL: Circular formation situated in the zone of librations.
SLOPES: Pretty steep slopes supporting a crater to the North and Wexler E to the East.
FLOOR: Flat floor.

NAME: WHEWELL
PERIOD: Eratosthenian (From -3.2 billions years to -1.1 billions years) ?
FACTS: Has given its name to a variety of natural calcium oxalate called whewellite.
GENERAL: Circular formation with bowl shape. Forms a remarkable trio with Cayley and Morgan.
SLOPES: Pretty steep slopes.
FLOOR: Rounded floor.

NAME: WICHMANN
PERIOD: Copernician (From -1.1 billions years to present days) ?
FACTS: Discovers the physical libration of the Moon.
GENERAL: Isolated circular formation with bowl shape situated to the South of a chain of hills in form of stone lance.
SLOPES: Few steep slopes supporting a North South oriented mountainous chain to the North.
FLOOR: Rounded floor.

NAME: WIDMANNSTATTEN
PERIOD: Birth period not found
FACTS: Researches in metallography. Has given his name to visible crystalline metallic structures on polite and attacked with nitric acid meteorites.

SLOPES: Few steep slopes.
FLOOR: Flat and extensive floor.
IAU_ORIGIN: Aloys Joseph Beck Edler von. German physicist (1754-1849). (Spelling changed from Widmanstätten.)

NAME: WILDT
PERIOD: Birth period not found
GENERAL: Isolated circular formation with bowl shape.
SLOPES: Few steep slopes.
FLOOR: Rounded floor.

NAME: WILHELM

GENERAL: Eroded circular formation.
SLOPES: Few steep slopes supporting Montanari to the South Lagalla to the South-West Wilhelm C to the North Wilhelm D to the North-East and Wilhelm O & E to the East.

SLOPES: Few steep slopes.

NAME: WILSON
PERIOD: Birth period not found

SLOPES: Pretty steep slopes supporting many craters whose Kircher to the West.

NAME: WINTHROP

NAME: WOHLER

FACTS: Discovers the aluminium and the bore in 1827. Succeeded in the first synthesis of an organic body (the urea) in 1828. Numerous works on organic bodies.
GENERAL: Isolated circular formation.
SLOPES: Few steep slopes supporting a craterlet to the West.
FLOOR: Flat floor.

NAME: WOLF
PERIOD: Pre-Imbrian (From -4.55 billions years to -3.85 billions years) ?
FACTS: Inventor in 1891 of a photographic research method of asteroids that permited him to discover more than 40 of them.
GENERAL: Wrecked and deformed formation.
SLOPES: Few steep slopes supporting small mountains to the South and to the East.

NAME: WOLLASTON

FLOOR: Rounded floor.

NAME: WRIGHT

FACTS: Selenographer.

NAME: WROTTESLEY
PERIOD: Upper Imbrian (From -3.8 billions years to -3.2 billions years)

SLOPES: Steep slopes supporting Wrottesley A to the North-West.

FLOOR: Flat floor. Central mountain.

NAME: WURZELBAUER

NAME: XENOPHANES

FLOOR: immense tormented Floor.  Central mountain.

NAME: YAKOVKIN
PERIOD: Birth period not found
FACTS: Specialist of the rotation and the shape of the Moon.

NAME: YANGEL

SLOPES: Few steep slopes.

NAME: YERKES

NAME: YOUNG
PERIOD: Pre-Imbrian (From -4.55 billions years to -3.85 billions years) ?

NAME: ZACH

NAME: ZAGUT

WALLS: Pretty high and tormented walls crushed by Zagut E to the East.
FLOOR: Flat floor supporting Zagut A to the center and a craterlet on the slope of Zagut E. Lines of crest.

NAME: ZAHRINGER
PERIOD: Eratosthenian (From -3.2 billions years to -1.1 billions years) ?
GENERAL: Isolated circular formation with bowl shape.
SLOPES: Few steep slopes.
FLOOR: Rounded floor.

NAME: ZENO

SLOPES: Few steep slopes supporting the trio Zeno D A & B to the South-West.

FLOOR: Flat floor.

NAME: ZINNER
PERIOD: Eratosthenian (From -3.2 billions years to -1.1 billions years) ?

SLOPES: Few steep slopes.
FLOOR: Rounded floor.

NAME: ZUPUS

FACTS: Jesuit
GENERAL: Irregular formation resembling to a small sea.
SLOPES: Few steep slopes supporting Zupus S to the North-East and Zupus A to the West.
